    <note>Wang(2) Jie [10241] Still listed as a Suzhou jinshi in 1190 (YLDD, 2368.7b. According to the Suzhou FZ, 78.13a, He was a Suzhou Wuxian person who went to Jinhua to study with Zhu(1) Xi [3257] and Lu(9) Zujian [7055]. While chronologically plausible, it seems more likely that his grandfather, Min [10240], moved to Jinhua. His dismissal as Tuzhi langzhong in 1206 is recorded in SHY:ZG, 73.36b. He was jinshi # 3. Zhen Dexiu, WJ, 46.25a-31b. CBD, 1, 106.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1206:  Dismissed (fangba) as Duzhi langzhong.宋集英殿修撰王公墓誌銘(真文忠公集46/27下)</note>
